com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetLookupValueRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetLookupValueRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GetLookupValueRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Retrieves the lookup display name (lookup code description) for the specific lookup values (lookup codes) on specified lookup columns. This API is used to retrieve the user friendly descriptions for specific code values when a package contains only the code value and the developer needs to display the user friendly description of the code in the user interface.

    Lookup value can only be retrieved for foreign key columns that have existing constraints. For detailed information on configuring relationships and lookups in the Siperian Hub, see "Configuring Foreign-Key Relationships Between Base Objects" in the "Building the Schema" chapter of the Siperian Hub Administrator Guide. You can use DescribeSiperianObjectRequest to get base object metadata, which provides information regarding columns that have lookups and the corresponding column identifiers.

    This API is intended to be used together with the GetLookupValuesRequest and SearchLookupValuesRequest APIs. The difference between these APIs is that the GetLookupValue API retrieves descriptions only for the specified code values, while the GetLookupValuesRequest and the SearchLookupValuesRequest return the list of valid lookup code values and lookup code descriptions for the specified lookup column.

    Required Parameters:

    • List of LookupField objects, each of which includes an identifier for the column and a lookup value for which to retrieve the lookup display name. You can use setLookupFields(ArrayList) to set the list of lookup values or use addLookupField(LookupField) to add a LookupField for a lookup value as shown in the following example.

    Usage Example:

    The following example gets the lookup display name for a lookup value 10 on the CATEGORY_CODE_ROWID column of C_SUB_CATEGORY base object:

    //You can retrieve a base object record for C_SUB_CATEGORY
    //using the GetRequest to get the categoryCodeRowid
    //For this example, a value of 10 is hard coded.

    String categoryCodeRowid ="10";
    GetLookupValueRequest getLookupRequest = new GetLookupValueRequest();
    LookupField lookupField = new LookupField();
    lookupField.setUid("COLUMN.C_SUB_CATEGORY|CATEGORY_CODE_ROWID ");
    lookupField.setValue(categoryCodeRowid);
    getLookupRequest.addLookupField(lookupField);
    GetLookupValueResponse response =
    (GetLookupValueResponse) sipClient.process(getLookupRequest);

    See Also:
    GetLookupValueResponse, LookupField, GetLookupValuesRequest, GetLookupValuesResponse, SearchLookupValuesRequest, SearchLookupValuesResponse, DescribeSiperianObjectRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetLookupValueResponse

    API Group: Data Steward
